youngest turners at work. The boy on the right is Joseph Allsbrook. Said he was 11 years old and been working steady for 3 months. Crescent Hosiery Mill.  Location: Scotland Neck, North Carolina.", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018677752/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/nclc/item/2018677755/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/nclc.02949", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/cph.3a20272", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018677755/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2018677755/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/nclc.02949/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/cph.3a20272/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2018677755"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["hine, lewis wickes"], "date": "1914-01-01", "dates": ["1914"], "description": ["1 photographic print."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-09-01T22:53:51.949Z", "group": ["nclc", "catalog-split-00", "catalog", "national-child-labor-committee", "main-catalog-split-00", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018677755/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/02900/02949_150px.jpg#h=107&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/02900/02949t.gif#h=108&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/02900/02949r.jpg#h=459&w=640", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/02900/02949v.jpg#h=734&w=1024"], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["scotland neck", "united states", "north carolina"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["2018677755", "http://www.loc.gov/item/20688602", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018677755", "http://www.loc.gov/item/ncl2004004146/pp", "2018-11-02t16:01:20"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "catalog", "prints and photographs division", "national child labor committee collection", "lot 7479"], "score": 26.468523, "shelf_id": "LOT 7479, v. 6, no. 3853 [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["girls", "hosiery industry", "textile machinery", "photographic prints", "united states", "textile mill workers", "scotland neck", "north carolina"], "timestamp": "2022-04-30T19:02:59.984Z", "title": "Nannie Coleson, looper who said she was 11 years old, and has been working in the Crescent Hosiery Mill for some months. Makes about $3 a week. Has been through the 5th grade in school. She is bright, but unsophisticated. Told investigator, \"There are other little girls in the mill too. One of them, says she's 13, but she doesn't look any older than me.\"  Location: Scotland Neck, North Carolina.", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018677755/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/nclc/item/2018677758/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/nclc.02952", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018677758/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2018677758/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/nclc.02952/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2018677758"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["hine, lewis wickes"], "date": "1914-01-01", "dates": ["1914"], "description": ["1 photographic print."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-09-01T22:53:51.949Z", "group": ["nclc", "catalog-split-03", "catalog", "national-child-labor-committee", "main-catalog-split-03", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018677758/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/02900/02952_150px.jpg#h=107&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/02900/02952t.gif#h=107&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/02900/02952r.jpg#h=455&w=640", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/02900/02952v.jpg#h=728&w=1024"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["scotland neck", "united states", "north carolina"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["201867775